# Course-builder video pipeline yoink audit

## Summary

**Verdict: yoink the choreography and contracts, not the implementation.** Course-builder has three useful ideas:

1. claim the local video record before creating external resources;
2. correlate Mux and Deepgram callbacks with one stable video-resource ID;
3. make each external transition an Inngest event.

The code itself is coupled to CourseBuilder's generic `ContentResource` database adapter, UploadThing, PartyKit, and parent lesson/post relationships. It also creates Mux assets from a public URL, while `joelclaw-video` phase 1 requires a Mux **Direct Upload** from a flagg-local file. The port therefore needs new package-owned types, Convex storage, and functions that consume joelclaw's already-normalized `mux/*` events. Sources: `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/video-uploaded.ts:45-194`; `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/index.ts:1-19`; joelclaw `packages/system-bus/src/webhooks/providers/mux.ts:16-22,47-54`.

The biggest hidden blocker is transcript ordering. Course-builder gives Deepgram a public `originalMediaUrl` immediately after UploadThing finishes. A flagg-local file sent directly to Mux does not leave behind an equivalent public source URL. `joelclaw-video` should order Deepgram only after it has a retrievable source, most naturally Mux's `highest.mp4` after `video.asset.static_rendition.ready`, or a deliberately signed archive URL. Sources: `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/order-transcript.ts:20-38`; `packages/core/src/providers/deepgram.ts:38-73`; [Mux static rendition guide](https://www.mux.com/docs/guides/enable-static-mp4-renditions).

Mux's current API confirms that CourseBuilder's `mp4_support: "standard"` is deprecated. New uploads should request `static_renditions: [{ "resolution": "highest" }]` inside `new_asset_settings`. That requests a progressive MP4, but no JSON can guarantee successful generation for every input: the rendition can be `ready`, `skipped`, or `errored`. Download readiness is a separate state from `video.asset.ready`. Sources: `packages/core/src/lib/mux.ts:126-149`; [current static rendition guide](https://www.mux.com/docs/guides/enable-static-mp4-renditions); [current create-direct-upload reference](https://www.mux.com/docs/api-reference/video/direct-uploads/create-direct-upload).

**Security finding:** CourseBuilder does not authenticate the Deepgram callback. The public catch-all route wraps the handler in a no-op `withSkill`, then the core callback trusts `request.body.results` and the query-string `videoResourceId`. Deepgram currently sends a `dg-token` header containing the submitting API key's identifier; the port must verify it or use callback Basic Auth. Sources: `apps/course-builder-web/src/app/api/coursebuilder/[...nextCourseBuilder]/route.ts:1-8`; `apps/course-builder-web/src/server/with-skill.ts:1-12`; `packages/core/src/lib/actions/index.ts:204-254`; [Deepgram callback authentication](https://developers.deepgram.com/docs/callback).

## Yoink map

### Per-function verdicts

| Course-builder function | Verdict | What to keep / why |
|---|---|---|
| `videoUploaded` | **rework** | Keep the DB-first ID claim, duplicate recovery, stable `passthrough`, and delete-Mux-on-local-write-failure pattern. Replace URL-based `createMuxAsset`, UploadThing fields, parent lesson replacement, PartyKit broadcasts, and user-shaped event data with a direct-upload state machine and Convex repository. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/video-uploaded.ts:45-124,126-194` |
| `videoReady` | **rework** | Keep correlation by `passthrough` and the state/duration/resolution update. Consume joelclaw's flat `mux/asset.ready` payload rather than CourseBuilder's nested `muxWebhookEvent`, and make the transition monotonic/idempotent. Drop PartyKit. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/video-ready.ts:12-57`; joelclaw `packages/system-bus/src/webhooks/providers/mux.ts:91-116` |
| `videoProcessingError` | **rework** | Keep an explicit terminal Mux-error transition and raw error receipt. Replace the CourseBuilder DB and PartyKit notification. Accept joelclaw `mux/asset.errored`. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/video-processing-error.ts:12-49` |
| `orderTranscript` | **rework** | Keep the small provider call and non-retriable missing-resource guard. Change the trigger: a local direct upload has no public `originalMediaUrl`; order Deepgram after a downloadable/presigned source exists. Persist the returned Deepgram `request_id`. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/order-transcript.ts:13-38`; `packages/core/src/providers/deepgram.ts:38-75` |
| `transcriptReady` | **skip** | It only reloads the video and broadcasts the transcript to PartyKit. `joelclaw-video` should expose a package event/state update; the consuming watch page or gateway can decide how to notify. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/transcript-ready.ts:11-41` |
| `addSrtToMuxAsset` | **rework** | Keep "asset must be ready before adding a text track." Replace the unbounded 20-second self-event loop with an explicit bounded state/retry policy. Do not delete the first text track: CourseBuilder can delete the wrong caption track, especially when Mux-generated subtitles also exist. Identify the Deepgram track by stored track ID or passthrough. Serve SRT from a durable signed/public URL Mux can fetch. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/add-srt-to-mux-asset.ts:15-83`; `packages/core/src/lib/mux.ts:15-75` |
| `removeCompletedVideo` | **skip** | UploadThing-specific polling and deletion. The destination's NAS/Garage original retention and TTL cleanup are a separate archive policy, not a Mux-processing function. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/remove-completed-video.ts:11-88` |
| `autoGeneratePostSeoDescription` | **skip** | Course product behavior: parent post/lesson lookup, user lookup, and co-gardener prompt dispatch. It does not belong in the standalone transport/package seam. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/auto-generate-post-seo-description.ts:13-98` |
| `generateTranscriptWithScreenshots` | **skip** | It is not registered in `coreVideoProcessingFunctions`; its trigger schema only carries `videoResourceId`, but the handler requires `event.data.srt`; and the Drizzle `getVideoResource` projection does not select `srt`. This path cannot work as written. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/index.ts:10-18`; `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/events/event-video-srt-ready-to-asset.ts:1-14`; `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/functions/generate-transcript-with-screnshots.ts:16-55`; `packages/adapter-drizzle/src/lib/mysql/index.ts:3065-3094` |
| `mergeSrtWithScreenshots` utility | **skip** | Heuristic screenshot insertion is watch-page/editorial behavior. It has hard-coded trigger words and mutable time-bucketing logic; it is not video ingest infrastructure. `packages/core/src/inngest/video-processing/utils.ts:5-102` |

